RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHOCKAZULU stalked the pace to the backstretch, pushed to the front leaving the three eighths then drew clear under steady urging. SMOKE AND BURN tracked the pace to the far turn, came two wide to the stretch then did not impact the winner but grabbed second. FOREVER GOLD set the pace off the rail for three eighths then was overtaken by the winner finished evenly. FORT YORK was four wide throughout and never a threat. HARROVIAN chased the pace three wide but weakened in the final furlong.
